02:33.961 --> 02:36.000
[Panting]

02:36.001 --> 02:38.791
[Ominous music plays]

03:06.649 --> 03:09.782
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:26.628 --> 03:28.250
This is a murder weapon.

03:30.961 --> 03:32.880
You didn't kill
your mother.

03:33.922 --> 03:36.630
I ran into her,
I knocked her off a balcony.

03:37.177 --> 03:39.630
If it wasn't me,
then how did she die?

03:40.310 --> 03:41.461
Complications.

04:08.442 --> 04:10.790
Have... have you been part
of this since...

04:11.419 --> 04:12.670
I was born?

04:12.671 --> 04:14.040
Mm.

04:14.065 --> 04:15.653
I wasn't that lucky.

04:18.747 --> 04:20.290
I remember a governess.

04:22.700 --> 04:24.583
She killed herself
at a party.

04:25.083 --> 04:27.227
And then there was
Mrs. Baylock.

04:27.415 --> 04:28.914
Did you know her?

04:28.915 --> 04:29.938
[Chuckles]

04:30.079 --> 04:31.988
I met her once
when I was just a girl.

04:31.989 --> 04:33.333
She terrified me.

04:36.083 --> 04:37.450
I don't know
what happened to her.

04:38.909 --> 04:40.075
She was murdered.

04:41.185 --> 04:42.618
Your father killed her...

04:42.619 --> 04:46.578
the same night
he tried to kill you...

04:46.579 --> 04:49.659
like Abraham
sacrificing Isaac.

04:52.271 --> 04:54.079
Abraham lived to become
the father of nations.

04:54.104 --> 04:55.864
My father was not
that lucky.

04:57.173 --> 05:00.213
I told you,
he wasn't your true father.

05:02.313 --> 05:04.989
I was brought in when you lived
in the White House.

05:05.733 --> 05:07.152
I raised you from afar.

05:07.153 --> 05:08.380
I raised myself.

05:09.023 --> 05:11.598
Consider me
a guiding hand.

05:14.733 --> 05:15.895
You were brought in
by who?

05:16.353 --> 05:19.112
I'm part of a group that exists
to protect you.

05:19.113 --> 05:21.708
There are many others who wish
you'd never been born.

05:22.380 --> 05:24.340
I'm starting to agree.

05:30.567 --> 05:31.692
I mean,
how deep does this go?

05:31.693 --> 05:33.891
How many people believe
I'm this Antichrist?

05:33.892 --> 05:35.793
- Honestly, I...
- Are you honest?

05:37.363 --> 05:39.965
Honestly, I don't know.

05:40.233 --> 05:42.772
I thought you had all
the answers.

05:42.773 --> 05:43.942
No one has
all the answers.

05:43.943 --> 05:45.813
Then this is
a waste of time.

05:45.853 --> 05:47.772
Some groups want
to worship you.

05:47.773 --> 05:49.112
Others want you dead.

05:49.113 --> 05:51.272
Like that guy who came after me?
Who was he?

05:51.273 --> 05:52.942
An unprotected pawn.

05:52.943 --> 05:54.942
Well, he almost succeeded
in trying to kill me.

05:54.943 --> 05:57.192
So much for you being
my guardian angel.

05:57.193 --> 05:59.692
I'm not your only source
of protection.

05:59.693 --> 06:02.192
There are many complex forces
at play.

06:02.193 --> 06:05.852
Some want you to fulfill what
they consider your destiny.

06:05.853 --> 06:10.312
[Chuckles]
What, to destroy the world?

06:10.926 --> 06:12.232
To fulfill God's will...

06:12.233 --> 06:15.301
to bring about
the second coming of Christ.

06:16.746 --> 06:19.715
Others want to protect
the status quo at all costs.

06:19.941 --> 06:21.402
It's only a matter of time

06:21.403 --> 06:22.942
before the Vatican's
forced to act.

06:22.943 --> 06:24.793
Wouldn't they want
this Second Coming?

06:24.925 --> 06:26.902
If the church is good
at one thing,

06:26.903 --> 06:28.062
it's retaining power.

06:28.332 --> 06:30.312
They don't roll over
for anyone.

06:31.067 --> 06:33.193
And then there are
the anarchists

06:33.435 --> 06:35.015
and the satanists.

06:36.856 --> 06:38.403
The list goes on.

06:41.121 --> 06:42.223
What do you want?

06:43.567 --> 06:45.286
Just being with you...

06:46.395 --> 06:47.770
is enough.

06:52.395 --> 06:53.739
Don't push me away.

06:55.598 --> 06:56.793
I'm a friend.

06:59.618 --> 07:03.707
Before you go,
tell me about Damascus.

07:05.442 --> 07:06.772
Nothing happened.

07:06.773 --> 07:10.112
It's all right. You...
You've got a lot to think about.

07:10.535 --> 07:12.062
We'll talk again.

07:12.063 --> 07:14.199
No, we won't.

07:14.853 --> 07:16.183
You can trust me.

07:22.733 --> 07:24.353
[Dog barking]

07:33.082 --> 07:34.293
Mom,
you showed him the shrine?

07:35.246 --> 07:36.676
How did he take it?

07:37.613 --> 07:38.597
He'll be back.

07:38.983 --> 07:41.272
Seems like he couldn't wait to
get the hell out of here.

07:42.098 --> 07:45.444
Give him time.
He's got nowhere else to go.

07:46.014 --> 07:49.099
His assailant was a theology
student... Hermon Seroyan.

07:49.271 --> 07:51.402
Doesn't seem to be connected to
any of the big players.

07:51.403 --> 07:53.732
Then how did he get
a Dagger of Megiddo?

07:54.186 --> 07:54.772
No idea.

07:55.826 --> 07:57.112
Seems like
he was acting alone.

07:57.113 --> 07:58.812
[Scoffs] Please.

07:58.813 --> 08:00.273
Nobody acts alone.

08:10.353 --> 08:13.353
Make sure you're planting them
at least 12 inches apart, okay?

08:13.354 --> 08:14.772
Father Esparza?

08:14.773 --> 08:16.652
- Simone, hi.
- Hi.

08:16.653 --> 08:18.903
I was just talking to your
parents a little while ago.

08:18.904 --> 08:20.062
Thank you
for checking in.

08:20.063 --> 08:21.943
- Can you talk?
- Of course.

08:22.959 --> 08:24.402
What's on your mind?

08:25.006 --> 08:26.022
This.

08:26.023 --> 08:27.852
It's Kelly's.

08:27.853 --> 08:29.312
Huh.

08:29.313 --> 08:32.812
Looks like your sister was
researching a religious story.

08:32.813 --> 08:35.982
Yeah, but her editor doesn't
know anything about it.

08:35.982 --> 08:39.652
Why are you
looking into this?

08:39.653 --> 08:41.902
Because it doesn't make
any sense.

08:41.903 --> 08:43.812
It may never make sense.

08:43.813 --> 08:46.112
I'm not talking about
Kelly's death,

08:46.113 --> 08:48.402
I'm talking about
how weird this is.

08:48.403 --> 08:51.193
She was researching
the Book of Revelation,

08:51.194 --> 08:53.112
- the Devil.
- No, I understand.

08:53.113 --> 08:54.772
You're searching
for a connection,

08:54.773 --> 08:56.902
you're looking for answers
that are not there.

08:57.160 --> 08:58.192
I'm not crazy.

08:58.193 --> 09:00.152
I didn't say you were,
honey,

09:00.153 --> 09:02.233
but you've suffered
a huge loss.

09:05.418 --> 09:06.403
Thanks, Father.

09:07.254 --> 09:08.098
Simone.

09:09.394 --> 09:10.480
Simone!

09:11.113 --> 09:13.062
[Siren wails in distance,
glass breaks]

09:13.063 --> 09:17.852
[Crows cawing loudly]

09:17.853 --> 09:21.273
[Choir singing ominously]

09:22.693 --> 09:23.902
Father!

09:23.903 --> 09:25.232
Father!

09:25.233 --> 09:26.772
What is it?

09:26.773 --> 09:28.902
You gotta see this.
Look.

09:28.903 --> 09:30.402
What is it?

09:30.403 --> 09:31.903
Look.

09:53.044 --> 09:58.504
Yes, Santa Maria dei Cappuccini
Maternity Hospital, Rome.

09:59.044 --> 10:00.660
Si, si, grazie.

10:01.844 --> 10:03.590
Burned down when?

10:05.152 --> 10:08.043
Uh, what about all
the hospital records?

10:08.044 --> 10:09.004
[Door opens]

10:10.165 --> 10:11.995
No, nothing else.
Thank you.

10:12.714 --> 10:15.246
You ever hear of
an Armitage Global?

10:16.004 --> 10:18.786
Yeah, international finance,
banking.

10:18.810 --> 10:20.551
Well, there's a big-shot...
Ann Rutledge.

10:20.733 --> 10:22.863
She has all this stuff of mine
in her house.

10:23.324 --> 10:24.638
What were you doing
at her house?

10:24.639 --> 10:25.847
She's got a ton of photos,

10:25.848 --> 10:27.517
all this stuff
from my childhood...

10:27.518 --> 10:28.887
my school uniform,
my first camera.

10:28.888 --> 10:30.057
Whoa.

10:30.058 --> 10:30.747
A whole shrine.

10:30.772 --> 10:32.232
- Of your stuff?
- Yeah.

10:32.718 --> 10:34.427
[Scoffs]

10:34.428 --> 10:35.559
No one's ever gonna believe
Ann Rutledge is your stalker.

10:35.669 --> 10:36.749
Well, you believe me.

10:37.152 --> 10:38.418
I think you've had a lot

10:38.419 --> 10:40.458
of very weird shit
going on.

10:40.459 --> 10:43.918
You've had a hell of a time
these past 10 days.

10:45.996 --> 10:48.328
Look, Simone and I went through
Kelly's stuff.

10:48.329 --> 10:51.248
She had all these notes on you,
bible stuff.

10:51.629 --> 10:53.249
We saw the tape.

10:54.669 --> 10:56.249
What did that old lady
do to you?

11:02.715 --> 11:03.637
What is all this?

11:04.169 --> 11:06.248
I can't explain it.

11:06.249 --> 11:08.618
Why did you Photoshop her
in here?

11:08.619 --> 11:11.878
I didn't Photoshop her,
she just appeared in them.

11:11.879 --> 11:13.918
I saw her here
in New York.

11:14.230 --> 11:17.288
The one in Damascus,
here in New York?

11:17.289 --> 11:18.301
I spoke to her.

11:18.599 --> 11:20.598
She...

11:20.919 --> 11:22.458
She what?

11:23.021 --> 11:25.101
She... ugh.

11:27.209 --> 11:28.378
Look, man, I get it.

11:28.379 --> 11:29.668
You've been through
a lot lately.

11:29.669 --> 11:31.418
What do you say
we get out of here

11:31.419 --> 11:32.828
and get some
much needed R&R?

11:33.387 --> 11:35.348
We got a few weeks
before we head out.

11:35.829 --> 11:38.708
I got us a gig in Kiev
for, uh...

11:38.709 --> 11:40.208
Harold Rolston.

11:40.209 --> 11:41.748
We don't work for Reuters.

11:41.749 --> 11:43.248
Yeah, well, we do now.

11:43.249 --> 11:45.066
Ceci fired us.

11:45.249 --> 11:46.918
Her bosses
gave her no choice.

11:46.919 --> 11:48.708
She...

11:48.918 --> 11:50.371
She didn't want to tell you
at the funeral.

11:52.215 --> 11:52.878
Well,
I can't deal with that.

11:52.879 --> 11:54.578
Now, if you want
to cover the Ukraine,

11:54.579 --> 11:56.539
you have to go without me.
I gotta stay here.

11:59.379 --> 12:02.418
Yeah, man, yeah.
Whatever you need.

12:02.419 --> 12:05.668
[Indistinct conversations]

12:05.669 --> 12:06.919
WOMAN: Thanks a lot.

12:14.918 --> 12:16.418
This doesn't make
any sense.

12:16.419 --> 12:17.828
Thorn's girlfriend,
she died a few days ago...

12:17.829 --> 12:19.378
freak accident.

12:19.379 --> 12:21.578
You think Thorn had something
to do with it?

12:21.579 --> 12:23.574
Not unless he summoned the earth
to swallow her whole.

12:24.379 --> 12:26.378
That's her...
the one that died

12:26.379 --> 12:27.722
in the sinkhole
up in the Bronx.

12:28.419 --> 12:29.748
Jesus.

12:29.749 --> 12:31.248
And the vic that got pinned
by the cab

12:31.249 --> 12:32.918
attacked Thorn the day
of her funeral.

12:32.919 --> 12:36.288
Meanwhile upstate,
Dumpster boy's teacher

12:36.652 --> 12:39.208
gets mauled to death by a pack
of wild dogs...

12:39.209 --> 12:40.748
the night that she dies.

12:40.749 --> 12:43.328
And guess who went to go visit
Professor Alpo

12:43.329 --> 12:44.789
only hours before he died.

12:48.566 --> 12:50.498
That's three dead
by freak accident.

12:50.847 --> 12:51.708
That's the holy trinity.

12:51.709 --> 12:53.378
That's crazy shit.

12:53.379 --> 12:55.499
Yeah.

13:00.749 --> 13:03.248
[Knock on door, door opens]

13:03.249 --> 13:04.828
WOMAN: Sir, he's here.

13:05.394 --> 13:06.949
Hold on.

13:07.709 --> 13:11.708
You know, there always
comes a moment

13:11.709 --> 13:13.618
when all your work...

13:13.619 --> 13:16.499
might just fall apart.

13:20.074 --> 13:21.090
Never gonna happen.

13:21.619 --> 13:23.958
I had a real boat once.

13:23.959 --> 13:27.458
Till it capsized
in the Caymans.

13:27.459 --> 13:29.618
What a nice surprise.

13:30.038 --> 13:32.877
- How long has it been?
- Since Preston Hall.

13:32.902 --> 13:34.498
It's great to see you
looking so well, Mr. Lyons.

13:34.499 --> 13:35.878
John... please.

13:35.879 --> 13:37.288
We're old pals from when

13:37.289 --> 13:39.208
I was whipping boy
to the First Lady.

13:39.209 --> 13:40.458
You were
her Chief of Staff.

13:40.459 --> 13:42.828
Oh, the same difference.
Drink?

13:43.222 --> 13:44.207
No, thanks.

13:46.644 --> 13:48.708
These always looked so intricate
and complicated.

13:49.902 --> 13:52.347
An inscrutable puzzle.

13:52.871 --> 13:55.378
Sharpens the mind,
helps when other parts

13:55.379 --> 13:57.918
aren't quite
shipshape anymore.

13:58.902 --> 14:00.288
But I doubt
you came here

14:00.289 --> 14:03.199
to talk about the indignities
of aging.

14:04.637 --> 14:06.328
I need a favor.

14:06.329 --> 14:07.829
Like that time
when you were 6

14:07.830 --> 14:10.418
and trashed all the crystal
vases in the East Wing?

14:10.419 --> 14:12.168
- [Chuckles]
- What a mess.

14:12.169 --> 14:14.613
You never did rat me out
to the First Lady.

14:15.249 --> 14:17.578
Wasn't hard for her
to figure out.

14:17.579 --> 14:21.378
There were a number of things
she held you responsible for.

14:22.347 --> 14:24.168
I did wonder why I was whisked
out of there.

14:25.097 --> 14:26.538
There were places
better suited

14:26.539 --> 14:29.748
to caring for a young boy
than the White House.

14:30.027 --> 14:31.458
We knew
those boarding schools

14:31.459 --> 14:33.708
would give you
everything you needed.

14:33.709 --> 14:36.788
What can I do for you?

14:36.789 --> 14:39.152
Are you here about that fracas
in Syria?

14:39.207 --> 14:40.418
No.

14:40.419 --> 14:42.748
I need some information.

14:42.749 --> 14:44.828
I'm not quite as inside
as I used to be.

14:44.829 --> 14:46.618
I doubt that.

14:47.504 --> 14:49.418
We all know people,
Damien.

14:49.668 --> 14:51.168
Ann Rutledge.

14:51.169 --> 14:52.618
You know her?

14:52.619 --> 14:55.748
I do.
We met at the White House.

14:55.749 --> 14:56.878
So she did work there?

14:56.879 --> 14:59.538
Why are you so interested
in her?

14:59.539 --> 15:02.749
Because she seems to have taken
an unnatural interest in me.

15:06.254 --> 15:07.644
I had a colleague...

15:08.558 --> 15:09.668
Brent Warner,

15:10.332 --> 15:11.878
senior economic advisor.

15:12.644 --> 15:15.708
Brent discovered Ann was
secretly funneling billions

15:15.709 --> 15:18.458
in military contracts
to Armitage.

15:19.168 --> 15:21.878
I thought Armitage Global was
a financial services company.

15:21.879 --> 15:23.618
They have many
interests...

15:23.619 --> 15:26.248
one of which is a private
security force...

15:26.249 --> 15:28.418
a mercenary army.

15:28.419 --> 15:30.288
I may have
come across them.

15:30.289 --> 15:31.748
They're everywhere.

15:32.176 --> 15:35.248
Brent was preparing to launch
an investigation.

15:35.249 --> 15:36.578
Ann got wind of it.

15:37.332 --> 15:38.288
What happened?

15:38.972 --> 15:40.828
It was Christmas eve.

15:40.829 --> 15:44.618
The tree that Brent, his wife,
and three young daughters

15:44.619 --> 15:48.708
had so beautifully decorated
with angels and twinkling lights

15:49.472 --> 15:51.498
mysteriously caught fire.

15:52.433 --> 15:55.652
Their house in Georgetown
went up in flames

15:55.918 --> 15:57.418
while the family slept.

15:59.246 --> 16:00.708
Everyone was incinerated.

16:02.488 --> 16:03.836
Another fire.

16:05.437 --> 16:07.498
The hospital
where I was born in Rome...

16:07.499 --> 16:09.578
burned down.

16:09.579 --> 16:12.579
They said it was
an accident.

16:17.703 --> 16:19.242
Be careful, Damien.

16:20.969 --> 16:24.748
I've seen more than
my fair share in my day.

16:24.749 --> 16:28.538
Not much surprises
or frightens me.

16:29.398 --> 16:32.918
Ann Rutledge does both.

16:45.999 --> 16:47.273
[Sighs]

16:47.298 --> 16:50.765
I went to see Father Esparza
to talk about Kelly's notes.

16:50.790 --> 16:53.031
You know what, actually,
I was thinking

16:53.056 --> 16:54.885
we should probably
leave that alone.

16:54.910 --> 16:56.266
Why?

16:56.410 --> 16:58.619
Just, what difference
would it make, you know?

16:59.511 --> 17:01.468
That's what
Father Esparza said.

17:01.493 --> 17:03.461
He said I was grasping
at straws.

17:04.780 --> 17:08.240
Okay, but then, Amani,
then I saw something.

17:10.499 --> 17:11.788
What?
What was it?

17:11.813 --> 17:13.483
[Sighs] You're gonna think
I'm insane.

17:13.509 --> 17:16.093
[Chuckles]
I wouldn't be too sure.

17:16.117 --> 17:17.867
I've heard a lot recently.

17:17.935 --> 17:19.476
[Sighs]

17:19.523 --> 17:22.022
I think Kelly is trying
to tell me something.

17:22.048 --> 17:24.497
I think she is trying
to communicate with me

17:24.521 --> 17:27.232
or send me a message
or something.

17:31.039 --> 17:32.879
[Horns honking]

18:01.619 --> 18:03.879
[Shutter clicks]

18:12.669 --> 18:14.039
[Sighs]

18:20.829 --> 18:22.168
[Camera shutter clicks]

18:22.169 --> 18:24.248
JOHN: How in the hell
could you allow

18:24.249 --> 18:26.249
something like this
to happen, Ann?

18:27.177 --> 18:31.187
An assassin strolls right up to
him on the street.

18:31.212 --> 18:32.421
Who was it?

18:32.446 --> 18:33.945
I'm working on it.

18:34.075 --> 18:35.531
Unacceptable.

18:35.624 --> 18:38.749
To me too.
We think he was acting alone.

18:38.774 --> 18:41.403
This man had one of
the Knives of Megiddo.

18:42.489 --> 18:43.445
No.

18:44.563 --> 18:47.249
How could you just leave
Thorn out there?

18:47.274 --> 18:48.859
Why didn't you
bring him in?

18:48.884 --> 18:50.213
Oh.

18:50.320 --> 18:52.569
You could have done
that yourself.

18:52.734 --> 18:55.653
If you were face to face with
him, why didn't you just...

18:55.678 --> 18:57.085
throw a net
over his head?

18:57.110 --> 19:00.124
And why didn't you bring this to
my attention immediately?

19:00.149 --> 19:02.429
John, stop worrying.

19:03.367 --> 19:06.601
We've been thinking it's time
for a change.

19:06.626 --> 19:08.165
Things <i> have</i> changed.

19:08.482 --> 19:09.859
Then he is ready.

19:09.884 --> 19:11.683
Not exactly.

19:12.919 --> 19:17.539
You know he has to accept
his role, embrace it.

19:17.564 --> 19:19.773
I'm not certain
that's in the cards.

19:20.316 --> 19:21.710
From everything we know
about the boy...

19:21.735 --> 19:23.364
He's 30.

19:23.389 --> 19:26.078
He's a kid that doesn't know
his ass from his elbow.

19:26.103 --> 19:27.062
Turn him over.

19:27.087 --> 19:28.586
We can't put a gun
to his head

19:28.611 --> 19:30.906
and just say, "Bring
about the apocalypse."

19:31.631 --> 19:34.840
There are very mysterious
forces at work.

19:35.512 --> 19:38.591
[Chuckles]
I brought you in.

19:38.616 --> 19:40.535
Remember, Ann?

19:40.560 --> 19:43.429
Oh, I do, John.

19:43.454 --> 19:46.124
But I know Damien
better than anyone.

19:46.149 --> 19:48.688
You're too close, sloppy.

19:48.713 --> 19:51.042
He knows about the hospital
in Rome.

19:51.067 --> 19:52.929
We can't leave him
out there.

19:52.954 --> 19:55.203
If someone else attempts
another assassination...

19:55.228 --> 19:56.835
That's always been
the risk.

19:57.720 --> 20:01.849
Do you know how much blood
I've spilled keeping him safe?

20:02.506 --> 20:04.890
Troy will take over.

20:04.915 --> 20:05.875
Troy?

20:06.280 --> 20:08.078
It's the next phase.

20:08.079 --> 20:09.868
Of whose plan?

20:10.602 --> 20:12.579
No offense, Troy,
but you're a moron.

20:13.319 --> 20:15.368
Is that so?

20:15.820 --> 20:18.367
Then tell us about the woman
in Damascus.

20:19.079 --> 20:21.868
She attacked
the Deliverer,

20:21.869 --> 20:25.028
she quoted Holly Liston,
the year five suicide,

20:25.029 --> 20:26.539
and then she spoke
in Latin.

20:27.449 --> 20:30.516
"My beloved son with whom
I am well pleased."

20:31.398 --> 20:34.818
Who?
What was she?

20:34.819 --> 20:38.028
Oh, don't pretend you have
the answers, either.

20:38.029 --> 20:40.368
Or that you'd last
five minutes

20:40.369 --> 20:43.937
face to face with the Deliverer,
who's also the Destroyer.

20:44.279 --> 20:50.199
This Damascus woman is the sign
we've been waiting for.

20:51.853 --> 20:55.102
Your coddling may have been
the answer in the past,

20:55.369 --> 20:57.318
but you're in
way over your head.

20:57.319 --> 20:59.078
Don't do this, John.

20:59.079 --> 21:02.118
There's no telling
what could happen

21:02.119 --> 21:04.528
if you try
to force things.

21:05.547 --> 21:07.336
Are you threatening me?

21:11.552 --> 21:13.342
You're done.

21:25.119 --> 21:28.209
♪♪

21:35.619 --> 21:37.669
[Sighs]

21:38.111 --> 21:39.451
[Horns honking]

21:51.963 --> 21:54.212
ANN: Where is he?

21:54.213 --> 21:56.783
Waiting right outside
Armitage...

21:56.837 --> 22:00.094
with a camera
and a laptop.

22:00.149 --> 22:01.689
Seems like he's doing
his homework.

22:04.189 --> 22:06.898
[Chuckles] He's running
surveillance on me.

22:06.899 --> 22:08.108
Looks like it.

22:08.109 --> 22:10.269
Don't let him
out of your sight.

22:10.414 --> 22:12.374
- Troy...
- Ann...

22:12.399 --> 22:16.568
I want you to know I had nothing
to do with John's decision.

22:16.569 --> 22:18.238
I was just as surprised
as you were.

22:18.239 --> 22:19.898
I'm sure.

22:19.899 --> 22:22.198
John's emotional.
We all are.

22:22.199 --> 22:23.488
But we need
to clear our heads

22:23.489 --> 22:25.148
to make sure this doesn't
get screwed up.

22:25.149 --> 22:26.488
Of course.

22:26.489 --> 22:28.028
There's certain things
you need to know about.

22:28.029 --> 22:30.028
We... we can't talk here.

22:30.029 --> 22:32.859
Meet me downstairs...
outside.

22:35.819 --> 22:36.898
[Cellphone rings]

22:36.899 --> 22:39.198
Hello?

22:39.199 --> 22:42.238
Andrha, hey.
Thanks for getting back to me.

22:42.239 --> 22:43.608
Yeah, great.

22:43.609 --> 22:46.608
Did you find out
about those daggers?

22:46.609 --> 22:49.989
All right, okay.

22:51.069 --> 22:54.068
That's it, yeah.

22:54.069 --> 22:56.898
It's one of seven.
It was excavated by a...

22:56.899 --> 23:00.238
Carl Bugenhagen decades ago.

23:00.239 --> 23:02.899
Is there still one of them
in that museum in Amman?

23:04.569 --> 23:08.109
How does something like that
just go missing?

23:14.989 --> 23:16.819
[Sighs]

23:28.859 --> 23:30.239
[Shutter clicking]

23:43.569 --> 23:46.068
I've dedicated my life
to our cause.

23:46.069 --> 23:48.148
You have been
an inspiration.

23:48.149 --> 23:50.528
I raised him
like he was my own child.

23:50.529 --> 23:52.028
Do you have children?

23:52.029 --> 23:53.398
A daughter.

23:53.399 --> 23:55.488
[Sighs]
So you understand.

23:55.489 --> 23:57.439
[Shutter clicking]

23:58.859 --> 24:00.358
What are you gonna do
with him?

24:00.359 --> 24:03.358
What you do
with a wild animal...

24:03.359 --> 24:05.148
I'm gonna break him.

24:05.149 --> 24:06.988
Be careful.

24:06.989 --> 24:08.238
I appreciate
your concern,

24:08.239 --> 24:10.028
but I'm not the one
who should be afraid.

24:10.029 --> 24:13.068
People are going to try to get
to Damien through you.

24:13.069 --> 24:15.068
Try to bribe you,
threaten you.

24:15.069 --> 24:16.358
You need to be strong.

24:16.359 --> 24:17.319
I will.

24:17.320 --> 24:18.858
Hold him close,

24:18.859 --> 24:20.488
but not too close.

24:20.489 --> 24:21.898
He'll use that.

24:21.899 --> 24:24.028
How?

24:24.029 --> 24:25.779
[Shutter clicking]

24:27.399 --> 24:30.898
He has certain needs...

24:30.899 --> 24:33.438
Blood, death.

24:33.439 --> 24:37.068
He's a war photographer
because he feeds off the pain.

24:37.069 --> 24:42.109
And women...
young girls, very young.

24:45.239 --> 24:48.148
Like your daughter.

24:48.149 --> 24:52.109
She sucked him dry.

24:53.439 --> 24:56.238
[Screams]
Don't hurt me!

24:56.239 --> 24:57.318
Help!

24:57.319 --> 24:59.438
Ohh! Help!

24:59.439 --> 25:00.898
You're crazy.
I didn't even touch you!

25:00.899 --> 25:02.399
Help!

25:05.319 --> 25:08.438
He's coming.

25:08.439 --> 25:10.568
He's coming for you.

25:10.569 --> 25:12.069
[Ominous music plays]

25:12.070 --> 25:13.238
Stop him!

25:13.239 --> 25:14.608
- [Car horn blares]
- Help!

25:14.609 --> 25:16.898
Help!

25:16.899 --> 25:18.278
You okay?

25:18.279 --> 25:20.069
Oh, Damien,
get out of here!

25:20.070 --> 25:21.528
- He'll come back.
- Who was he?

25:21.529 --> 25:24.148
He wants to kill you.
Please, just get out of here.

25:24.149 --> 25:25.238
Don't!

25:25.239 --> 25:27.199
DAMIEN: Hey!

25:28.859 --> 25:30.528
MAN:
What are you doing?

25:30.529 --> 25:33.239
[Ominous music continues]

25:40.899 --> 25:42.278
Wait!

25:42.279 --> 25:44.359
[Horn blares]

25:47.109 --> 25:48.359
Move!

25:52.109 --> 25:54.068
[Grunts]

25:54.069 --> 25:55.939
[Screams]

26:04.989 --> 26:06.859
Move!

26:17.399 --> 26:19.779
MAN: Hey, watch
what you're doing!

26:22.569 --> 26:24.398
[Grunts]

26:24.399 --> 26:25.568
Out of the way!

26:25.569 --> 26:27.238
Help!

26:27.239 --> 26:29.818
Mommy!

26:29.819 --> 26:31.318
- Tiago!
- MAN: Somebody help her!

26:31.319 --> 26:33.358
Mommy!

26:33.359 --> 26:35.488
- Mommy!
- [Train horn blares]

26:35.489 --> 26:39.149
Mommy!
Mommy!

26:43.819 --> 26:45.319
Move!

26:47.149 --> 26:50.238
WOMAN:
Hey, on the steps!

26:50.239 --> 26:54.149
[Ominous music plays]

26:59.069 --> 27:01.398
Help him!

27:01.399 --> 27:03.358
[Grunting]

27:03.359 --> 27:06.899
[Screaming]

27:19.461 --> 27:21.580
[Sobs] Thank you.

27:21.581 --> 27:24.130
Looks like
he's gonna be okay.

27:24.131 --> 27:26.080
You look after your mom,
okay?

27:26.081 --> 27:28.131
MAN: Bravo, buddy.

27:33.581 --> 27:36.290
[Applause]

27:36.291 --> 27:39.630
MAN #2:
Well done, well done.

27:39.631 --> 27:42.170
MAN #3: <i> Attention,
due to an emergency,</i>

27:42.171 --> 27:44.170
<i>platform "B" is now closed.</i>

27:44.171 --> 27:46.210
WOMAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
keep moving, please.

27:46.211 --> 27:47.790
<i>All other platforms
remain open.</i>

27:47.791 --> 27:49.630
[Chatter]

27:49.631 --> 27:54.250
MAN #4: I have to get approval.
It's gonna be a minute.

27:54.251 --> 27:56.131
WOMAN:
Nice, orderly fashion.

27:56.132 --> 27:58.420
Keep right, please.

27:58.421 --> 28:01.541
This lane is closed right now.
Take the stairs.

28:01.542 --> 28:05.001
[Ominous music plays]

28:25.581 --> 28:29.500
[Woman sobbing]

28:29.501 --> 28:30.841
ANN: What is it?

28:33.915 --> 28:35.294
It's Mr. Hendrie.

28:35.295 --> 28:36.874
Is he all right?

28:36.875 --> 28:38.294
He's been killed.

28:38.295 --> 28:40.745
[Sobbing]

28:58.085 --> 29:00.665
[Siren wails in distance]

29:13.205 --> 29:16.915
We didn't have any champagne,
so this will have to do.

29:18.455 --> 29:22.085
Damien Thorn...
hero of the day.

29:26.875 --> 29:28.414
What's wrong?

29:28.415 --> 29:30.244
"What's wrong?"

29:30.245 --> 29:32.244
Uh, a man was torn apart today
and died.

29:32.245 --> 29:36.084
Yeah. And someone else didn't
die... the kid you saved.

29:36.085 --> 29:37.744
Take the win.

29:37.745 --> 29:41.374
It seems wherever I go,
death follows.

29:41.375 --> 29:44.124
This is New York, bro.

29:44.125 --> 29:45.794
There's
20 million people.

29:45.795 --> 29:48.294
I'm sure some guy in the Bronx
had a heart attack.

29:48.295 --> 29:50.294
Is that supposed to be
your fault, too?

29:50.295 --> 29:51.454
You know what I mean.

29:51.455 --> 29:53.204
Look,
you tried to save Kelly.

29:53.205 --> 29:55.874
Same thing goes for that guy
who got hit by the cab.

29:55.875 --> 29:57.294
And if you had the chance,

29:57.295 --> 29:59.914
you would have tried to save
the guy at the escalator.

29:59.915 --> 30:01.744
That's who you are.

30:01.745 --> 30:04.294
But you can't save
everyone.

30:04.295 --> 30:07.125
You're not God.

30:11.295 --> 30:13.004
All right.

30:13.005 --> 30:15.124
Why don't you try
to get some sleep

30:15.125 --> 30:17.124
and I'll call you
in the morning.

30:17.125 --> 30:19.795
All right.

30:34.915 --> 30:38.125
[Phone ringing in distance]

30:47.045 --> 30:48.874
[Object slams]

30:48.875 --> 30:51.794
Looks like you've been barking
up the wrong tree.

30:51.795 --> 30:54.454
Your boy Thorn
is a regular Eagle Scout.

30:54.455 --> 30:56.294
He rescued a kid
off the tracks?

30:56.295 --> 31:01.834
Yeah, just as the subway was
rolling in... a real hero.

31:01.835 --> 31:03.794
It says here
there was another death.

31:03.795 --> 31:05.204
Unrelated accident.

31:05.205 --> 31:07.164
Some guy bought it in another
part of the station.

31:07.165 --> 31:09.454
Come on, shut this down.
Time to get some sleep.

31:09.455 --> 31:10.705
Let's go.

31:12.165 --> 31:14.335
Get a life.

31:24.705 --> 31:28.245
♪♪

31:38.375 --> 31:40.414
[Snarls]

31:40.415 --> 31:42.705
[Eerie whispering]

31:47.915 --> 31:50.125
[Snarling]

31:52.455 --> 31:56.045
[Screaming]

32:03.955 --> 32:05.084
[Dog whines]

32:05.085 --> 32:06.955
[Panting]

32:10.745 --> 32:13.795
[Gothic choir sings
ominously]

32:18.651 --> 32:21.571
[Knock on door]

32:30.861 --> 32:33.031
[Knock on door]

32:36.651 --> 32:38.860
I came as soon as I heard.

32:38.861 --> 32:41.320
I'm fine.

32:41.321 --> 32:44.700
I brought sushi.
[Chuckles]

32:44.701 --> 32:47.360
Chef Masa is a dear
old friend of mine.

32:47.361 --> 32:49.071
He prepared it himself.

32:59.411 --> 33:01.490
Was that man
really after me,

33:01.491 --> 33:04.570
or was he just someone
you wanted out of your way?

33:04.571 --> 33:07.320
Both.

33:07.321 --> 33:09.950
I won't do this.

33:09.951 --> 33:13.410
That's not how this works.

33:13.411 --> 33:16.650
This morning,
you had all the answers.

33:16.651 --> 33:20.360
Now you don't.

33:20.361 --> 33:23.110
I said no one
has all the answers.

33:23.111 --> 33:25.651
I didn't say
there aren't any.

33:29.991 --> 33:32.650
How did you get this?

33:32.651 --> 33:36.070
I just...
I destroyed it.

33:36.071 --> 33:38.700
I deleted all the files.

33:38.701 --> 33:40.071
[Slam]

33:46.411 --> 33:48.570
ANN:
It's such an amazing shot.

33:48.571 --> 33:51.780
If you'd had the temerity
to publish it,

33:51.781 --> 33:53.490
maybe the U.N.
would have sent in

33:53.491 --> 33:56.320
its Peacekeepers
months earlier.

33:56.321 --> 33:59.490
A photo like this could have
saved thousands of lives.

33:59.491 --> 34:00.990
No.

34:00.991 --> 34:03.410
There was nothing
anyone could have done.

34:03.411 --> 34:05.450
You really believe that?

34:05.451 --> 34:06.780
It's true.
I mean, we...

34:06.781 --> 34:07.990
we knew they were coming.

34:07.991 --> 34:09.610
The warlords
and militia

34:09.612 --> 34:12.409
swept through the back country
that whole summer.

34:12.411 --> 34:15.741
With the rains,
the river was flooded.

34:16.295 --> 34:17.416
The village was cut off.

34:17.417 --> 34:19.505
You got in.

34:32.206 --> 34:35.335
♪♪

34:35.335 --> 34:37.255
[Paper rustles]

34:47.376 --> 34:50.375
The night
they came through,

34:50.376 --> 34:54.295
the villagers ran
into the fields.

34:54.295 --> 34:56.005
Uh...

34:56.005 --> 34:59.295
The guerrillas
chased them.

34:59.296 --> 35:05.005
Hacked down the tall grass,
the bodies...

35:05.006 --> 35:07.915
with machetes.

35:07.916 --> 35:13.466
Those who didn't run were
rounded up, slaughtered.

35:15.876 --> 35:18.005
I was in the field.

35:18.006 --> 35:21.545
No one saw me.

35:21.546 --> 35:25.625
One woman was in labor.
She couldn't run.

35:25.626 --> 35:29.585
They dragged her husband
into the square.

35:29.586 --> 35:32.625
And the warlords waited
with this man

35:32.626 --> 35:37.415
while his wife gave birth...
and she was screaming...

35:37.416 --> 35:41.375
for hours.

35:41.376 --> 35:43.465
[ <i> Woman screams</i> ]

35:43.466 --> 35:47.165
The fields were filled
with the screams of the dying.

35:47.166 --> 35:50.295
The militia,
they just stood there, smoking,

35:50.296 --> 35:52.915
laughing at her screams.

35:52.916 --> 35:57.626
The flames burned higher.

36:00.666 --> 36:03.626
When that baby's head
was finally showing...

36:06.466 --> 36:08.125
[ <i> Baby crying</i> ]

36:08.126 --> 36:11.875
...they ripped it
out of her...

36:11.876 --> 36:15.046
and threw it on the fire.

36:17.296 --> 36:20.006
Its first breath
was a scream.

36:25.376 --> 36:29.125
After that...

36:29.126 --> 36:32.336
they killed them all.

36:36.876 --> 36:39.295
And you blame me

36:39.296 --> 36:42.165
for destroying that photo.

36:42.166 --> 36:47.045
I blame you
for those deaths.

36:47.046 --> 36:50.915
The evil you felt
that night...

36:50.916 --> 36:53.125
that you always feel...

36:53.126 --> 36:56.465
that you keep
running away from,

36:56.466 --> 36:58.465
it comes from inside
of you.

36:58.466 --> 37:04.375
It's what kept you alive
when that man attacked you.

37:04.376 --> 37:06.045
It's what kept you
alive today.

37:06.046 --> 37:07.625
Bullshit!

37:07.626 --> 37:10.465
You just want me to buy
this whole...

37:10.466 --> 37:12.625
Antichrist head game
of yours.

37:12.626 --> 37:14.965
What's your explanation?

37:14.966 --> 37:18.005
You're just like
that baby...

37:18.006 --> 37:21.505
born in the fire.

37:21.506 --> 37:25.625
There <i> was</i> evil there
that night, but...

37:25.626 --> 37:27.965
I had nothing to do
with it.

37:27.966 --> 37:32.255
It was those men who ripped
that baby from its mother.

37:32.256 --> 37:35.085
And what happened to them?

37:35.086 --> 37:38.335
Government troops
captured them.

37:38.336 --> 37:42.205
Hanged them at sunrise.

37:42.206 --> 37:45.505
[Chuckles]

37:45.506 --> 37:48.295
I guess there is a God
after all.

37:48.296 --> 37:50.415
Not God.

37:50.416 --> 37:52.416
Something else.

37:54.966 --> 37:57.125
You're proof
of the magical.

37:57.126 --> 37:58.625
I'm not.

37:58.626 --> 38:00.965
Once you accept
who you are,

38:00.966 --> 38:03.255
things will be
so much easier.

38:03.256 --> 38:05.625
You have to trust me.

38:05.626 --> 38:07.585
I'd never do anything
to hurt you.

38:07.586 --> 38:09.465
[Laughs]

38:09.466 --> 38:12.165
How can I believe that?

38:12.166 --> 38:15.965
You better leave.

38:15.966 --> 38:20.205
Of course.
It's late, and your exhausted.

